7172177027284471082.desc: RECIPE: 8 onions, sliced - sauté in butter and olive oil with salt pepper and garlic til soft, turn down heat and caramelize. Add chopped sage and 8 cups beef stock. Bring to a boil. Add 1/4 cup lemon juice. Mix 1 tablespoon cornstarch with 3 tablespoons water, mix well, stir into soup. Bring back up to a boil, reduce to simmer. Taste for seasoning. Ladel into oven safe bowls. Top with layer favorite cheese, then layer toasted gluten free bread, second layer of cheese. Broil on low 4-5 min til brown and bubbly, top with rosemary, enjoy! #glutenfree #soup #soupseason #souptok #comfort #comfortfood #yummy #food #foodinclusive #foodshare #yum #fyp #foryou #foryoupage #recipe #onmollysplate

challenges.desc: For the moments that make you say, “hey, isn’t this easy?!”

stickerText: SUPER easy one - keep the crackers/bread/pretzels on the side! Things like cheese and charcuterie are often naturally gluten free - but if you put the gluten-containing ingredients ON the board, it’s contaminated; serve separately, and have your allergic guest serve themselves first!
